&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EPSOM AND ST HELIER UNIVERSITY HOSPITALS NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Clinical Fellow in General Anaesthesia &amp; Simulation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£49,036 + Allowances and LW &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time - 12 month fixed term contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To start February 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Senior Clinical Fellow to join our Anaesthetic team, and further develop on their anaesthetic and simulation experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are two posts available for a full time Senior Clinical Fellow in General Anaesthesia/Simulation to start in February 2021. The post is for a fixed term period of 12 months with the possibility of extension.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for the successful applicant to gain experience in general anaesthetics in a supportive department and to have protected simulation sessions. The post holder will be required to work on the on call rota on a 1:8 basis at either Epsom Hospital or St Helier Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fellowship is aimed at those who wish to build on their personal teaching experience, develop expertise in educational theory and practice, and undertake supervised educational research. Although an enthusiasm for teaching is a prerequisite, no assumptions will be made about formal knowledge of educational theory or practice. Hands-on teaching will be central to the post, as will a critical engagement with educational issues around providing postgraduate training in a changing context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Paul Bathke Job title Consultant Anaesthetist &lt;br /&gt;Email address - Paul.bathke@nhs.net Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Paul Bathke, Consultant Anaesthetist Paul.bathke@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
